displayed_text: Patient: There’s the first one is – is whoops, one of them is from um March of fifteen to um November of fifteen and then the second one is January of sixteen to March of seventeen. Doctor: Okay. And I forgot, I think I asked you this before, do you have a nephrologist? Patient: No. I do not. Doctor: This is your primary care person checking it right? Patient: Yeah. But whoever was doing – ordering the vitals. Doctor: Yeah, gotcha. Patient: The vitals, the vitals, the uh what do they call it, comes in a comprehensive uh metabolic, metabolic panel. Doctor: Yeah, you were as high as one point seven five, May twenty-sixteen? Patient: No I think in fifteen I was even higher than that. Doctor: And then um (papers shuffling) Patient: I don’t know that your medication is the one that’s the problem. Doctor: It’s probably not.
